register

public void register(java.lang.String name,
                     javax.servlet.Servlet servlet)
Register a (name, servlet) for future "get(name)" requests.

The name must be HTTP-safe -- see RFC 1945 for details.

If the same Servlet is registered multiple times, or multiple threads attempt the simultaneous register and unregister of a Servlet, then the order of "Servlet.init()" and "Servlet.destroy()" is not defined.

Specified by:
register in interface ServletRegistry
See Also:
